snippet: Honolulu city crews on Thursday began clearing the final section of one of the nation’s largest homeless encampments, once home to hundreds of people.
abstract: Honolulu begins clearing final section of encampment of homeless people near Waikiki, one of largest such encampments in nation; officials say around 100 remaining homeless from original population that numbered in the hundreds, will be moved to shelters.
lead_paragraph: Honolulu city crews on Thursday began clearing the final section of one of the nation’s largest homeless encampments, once home to hundreds of people.

headline.print_headline: Hawaii: Homeless Encampment Is Being Cleared
